Assignment No-1 

**Q1.  Create a static web page which defines all text formatting tags, all heading tags of HTML.**

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Q1 - Text Formatting and Headings</title>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Headings -->
  <h1>This is Heading 1</h1>
  <h2>This is Heading 2</h2>
  <h3>This is Heading 3</h3>
  <h4>This is Heading 4</h4>
  <h5>This is Heading 5</h5>
  <h6>This is Heading 6</h6>

  <!-- Text formatting tags -->
  <p><b>Bold</b> and <i>Italic</i></p>
  <p><u>Underline</u> and <mark>Highlighted</mark></p>
  <p>H<sub>2</sub>O (subscript), X<sup>2</sup> (superscript)</p>
  <p><del>Deleted</del> and <ins>Inserted</ins></p>
</body>
</html>

   ** Q2.  Design a page having suitable background color and text color with title “My First Web Page” 
           using all the attributes of the Font tag.**

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>My First Web Page</title>
</head>
<!-- bgcolor sets page background color, text sets text color -->
<body bgcolor="lightblue" text="black">
  <h1 align="center">My First Web Page</h1>

  <!-- font tag with attributes (deprecated but shown here) -->
  <p><font face="Arial" size="4" color="red">This is red Arial text.</font></p>
  <p><font face="Times New Roman" size="5" color="green">This is green Times text.</font></p>
  <p><font face="Courier New" size="3" color="blue">This is blue Courier text.</font></p>
</body>
</html>


**Q3.  Write a HTML program for the demonstration of Lists. 
Unordered List 
Ordered List **

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Q3 - Lists</title>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Unordered list (bullets) -->
  <h2>Unordered List</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Apple</li>
    <li>Mango</li>
    <li>Banana</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- Ordered list (numbers) -->
  <h2>Ordered List</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Step 1</li>
    <li>Step 2</li>
    <li>Step 3</li>
  </ol>
</body>
</html>

**Q4. Write a HTML program for demonstrating Hyperlinks. 
Navigation from one page to another. 
Navigation within the page.**

File 1: index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Q4 - Hyperlinks</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Hyperlink Example</h1>

  <!-- Link to another page -->
  <p><a href="about.html">Go to About Page</a></p>

  <!-- Link within the same page -->
  <p><a href="#section2">Go to Section 2</a></p>

  <h2 id="section1">Section 1</h2>
  <p>This is section 1.</p>

  <h2 id="section2">Section 2</h2>
  <p>This is section 2.</p>
</body>
</html>

   File 2: about.html
   
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>About Page</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>About Page</h1>
  <p>This is the second page.</p>
  <p><a href="index.html">Back to Home</a></p>
</body>
</html>

**Q5. Create a static web page using table tags of HTML.(create Timetable)**

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Q5 - Timetable</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Class Timetable</h1>

  <!-- Simple table with border -->
  <table border="1" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0">
    <tr>
      <th>Time</th>
      <th>Mon</th>
      <th>Tue</th>
      <th>Wed</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>9–10</td>
      <td>Math</td>
      <td>English</td>
      <td>Science</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>10–11</td>
      <td>History</td>
      <td>Math</td>
      <td>Computer</td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</body>
</html>

  **Q6. Create a webpage to include images using HTML tag.**

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Q6 - Images</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Images Example</h1>

  <!-- Local image (must be in same folder) -->
  <img src="myphoto.jpg" alt="My Photo" width="200" height="200">

  <!-- Online image -->
  <img src="https://www.mitacsc.ac.in/uploads/1730959639_872888_1457525865_793789_logo.png" alt="Placeholder Image">
</body>
</html>

**Q7. Create a personal webpage using various heading levels, paragraphs, and lists to describe 
            yourself and your interests.**


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Q7 - My Personal Page</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Hi, I am Alex</h1>

  <h2>About Me</h2>
  <p>I am a student who loves coding and technology.</p>

  <h2>My Interests</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Coding</li>
    <li>Music</li>
    <li>Sports</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>My Goals</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Learn HTML and CSS</li>
    <li>Build my own website</li>
    <li>Start a blog</li>
  </ol>
</body>
</html>

